00:00:02.710 --> 00:00:09.389
Castor oil is most widely used in cosmetics,
soaps, textiles, massage oils and even medicines.

00:00:09.389 --> 00:00:15.240
Here are some medicinal and therapeutic benefits
of castor oil.

00:00:15.240 --> 00:00:21.460
Castor oil is known to treat skin problems
like sunburn, acne, dry skin and stretch marks.

00:00:21.460 --> 00:00:28.460
it also helps cure infections like warts,
boils, athlete's foot and chronic itching.

00:00:28.779 --> 00:00:34.300
An active compound found in castor oil effectively
treats ringworms which is a common and stubborn

00:00:34.300 --> 00:00:37.960
skin problem across all age groups.

00:00:37.960 --> 00:00:43.640
Castor oil when applied to the skin penetrates
deep and stimulates the production of collagen

00:00:43.640 --> 00:00:50.640
and elastin. this delays appearance of wrinkles
and fine lines, making the skin smother, softer

00:00:50.949 --> 00:00:53.859
and younger.

00:00:53.859 --> 00:00:59.440
Castor oil promotes hair growth by boosting
blood circulation to the follicles. The oil

00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:06.190
also have omega-6 essential for fatty acids,
responsible for healthy hair.

00:01:06.190 --> 00:01:11.970
Castor oil's anti-fungal, anti bacterial,
and anti-viral properties can help treat scalp

00:01:11.970 --> 00:01:17.360
infections like bald patches and itchy scalp.

00:01:17.360 --> 00:01:23.619
Castor oil is a powerful laxative useful for
effectively treating constipation.

00:01:23.619 --> 00:01:29.950
Castor oil is often used for fading scars.
It is crammed with omega-3 fatty acids that

00:01:29.950 --> 00:01:31.579
help reduce pigmentation.

00:01:31.579 --> 00:01:37.700
Anti inflammatory property of castor oil makes
it ideal massage oil for relieving joint pain,

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:42.000
nerve inflammation and sore muscles.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:47.250
Castor oil has been scientifically proven
to treat mild surface tumors.

